		<description><html:strong>Example 1:</html:strong> The snippet <html:strong>&quot;%insert_evaluator_anchor_here% Date().toDateString();%insert_evaluator_anchor_here%&quot;</html:strong> will insert the current date.</description>
		<description><html:strong>Example 2:</html:strong> The snippet <html:strong>&quot;%insert_evaluator_anchor_here%.userAgent;%insert_evaluator_anchor_here%&quot;</html:strong> will insert the application's User Agent.</description>
		<description></description>
		<description class="warning">WARNING!!!!</description>
		<description class="warning">The expresion inside the Evaluator placeholders must always return a string.</description>
		<description class="warning">If you have no notion at all of what evaluating JavaScript code means/does, DO NOT USE this feature.</description>
	</tooltip>
